# Accessibility Rules (WCAG 2.1 AA)

## Structure

- One `<main>` per page; use `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<footer>` landmarks.
- `<section>` and `<article>` elements must have an accessible name via `aria-labelledby` or `aria-label`.
- Heading levels must be sequential — never skip from `h2` to `h4`.

## Images & Icons

- Informative images: descriptive `alt` text.
- Decorative images: `alt=""`.
- SVG icons acting as buttons/links: add `aria-label` on the parent or a visually-hidden `<span>`.

## Keyboard & Focus

- Every interactive element must be Tab-reachable.
- Never set `outline: none` without a visible focus replacement.
- Add a skip-to-content link as the first child of `<body>`.

## Color & Contrast

- Normal text: contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1.
- Large text (≥ 18 pt / 14 pt bold): contrast ratio ≥ 3:1.
- Never convey information through color alone.

## Quick axe check

```bash
npx axe http://localhost:4321 --exit
```
